#  EXP 6 (Functions + Date Operations)

### 1. Display empno, ename, dept name instead of deptno (using CASE in MySQL)

```sql id="e6q1"
SELECT EMPNO, ENAME, CASE DeptNo WHEN 10 THEN 'RESEARCH' WHEN 20 THEN 'ACCOUNTING' WHEN 30 THEN 'SALES' WHEN 40 THEN 'OPERATIONS' END AS DNAME FROM Employee;
```

### 2. Display your age in days

```sql id="e6q2"
SELECT DATEDIFF(CURDATE(),'2000-01-01') AS AGE_IN_DAYS;
```

### 3. Display your age in months

```sql id="e6q3"
SELECT TIMESTAMPDIFF(MONTH,'2000-01-01',CURDATE()) AS AGE_IN_MONTHS;
```

### 4. Display the current date as formatted text

```sql id="e6q4"
SELECT DATE_FORMAT(CURDATE(),'%D %M %W %Y');
```

### 5. Display formatted joining message for each employee

```sql id="e6q5"
SELECT CONCAT(ENAME,' has joined the company on ',DATE_FORMAT(HIREDATE,'%W %D %M %Y')) FROM Employee;
```

### 6. Scott has joined the company on formatted date

```sql id="e6q6"
SELECT CONCAT(ENAME,' has joined the company on ',DATE_FORMAT(HIREDATE,'%W %D %M %Y')) FROM Employee WHERE ENAME='SCOTT';
```

### 7. Find the nearest Saturday after current date

```sql id="e6q7"
SELECT DATE_ADD(CURDATE(), INTERVAL (7 - DAYOFWEEK(CURDATE()) + 7) % 7 DAY);
```

### 8. Display current time

```sql id="e6q8"
SELECT CURTIME();
```

### 9. Display the date three months before current date

```sql id="e6q9"
SELECT DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 3 MONTH);
```

### 10. Display employees who joined in December

```sql id="e6q10"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE MONTH(HIREDATE)=12;
```

### 11. Display employees where first 2 chars of hiredate match last 2 digits of salary

```sql id="e6q11"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE LEFT(DAY(HIREDATE),2)=RIGHT(SAL,2);
```

### 12. Display employees whose 10% salary equals year of joining

```sql id="e6q12"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE (SAL*0.10)=YEAR(HIREDATE);
```

### 13. Display employees who joined before 15th month (interpreted as month < 6 for safety)

```sql id="e6q13"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE MONTH(HIREDATE)<6;
```

### 14. Display employees who joined before 15th day of month

```sql id="e6q14"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE DAY(HIREDATE)<15;
```

### 15. Display employees whose joining year equals deptno (logical interpretation)

```sql id="e6q15"
SELECT * FROM Employee WHERE YEAR(HIREDATE)=DeptNo;
```
